# Class: obo:GENEPIO_0100565 (minor quality control issues identified datum)

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000114 obo:GENEPIO_0100565 "ready-for-release")
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 obo:GENEPIO_0100565 "A data item which is a statement confirming that quality control processes were carried out and that the sequence did not meet the assessment criteria, however the issues detected were minor."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000118 obo:GENEPIO_0100565 "minor quality control issues identified"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(terms:contributor obo:GENEPIO_0100565 <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1107-9135>)
AnnotationAssertion(terms:contributor obo:GENEPIO_0100565 <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9578-0788>)
AnnotationAssertion(terms:date obo:GENEPIO_0100565 "2023-01-23T00:42:19.315Z"^^xsd:dateTime)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment obo:GENEPIO_0100565 "Example: This statement may be used in conjunction with the quality control determination statement \"sequence failed quality control\" to communicate that the reasons why the sequence did not meet the assessment criteria. Minor issues may include phenomena that the analyst should review e.g. amplicons detected in the negative control sequence or more mutations than expected based on the reference sequence. The details of the issues can be described in the \"quality control details\" field. Note: quality control here refers to quality of the raw reads, consensus sequence or assembly, not the qaulity of analytical results e.g. lineage assignment."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label obo:GENEPIO_0100565 "minor quality control issues identified datum"@en)
SubClassOf(obo:GENEPIO_0100565 obo:GENEPIO_0100662)

